    <p>
    <a href="/blog/making-a-maze/">read more</a>
    
    /
    
    <a href="/blog/making-a-maze/#comments">
        7 comments
    </a>
    
    
    </p>
</div>




<h2>
    <a href="/blog/doi-to-bibtex/">DOI to BibTeX</a>
</h2>




<h6 class="post-meta">
    Posted by:
    
    <a href="/blog/author/christian/">christian</a>
    
    
    
    
    on 3 Apr 2017
</h6>







<p>The Digital Object Identifier (DOI) resolution service at <a href="http://www.doi.org/">doi.org</a> exposes an API for retrieving the BibTeX markup for a reference given its DOI. The following Python 3 script takes a DOI on the command line and returns the BibTeX. For example,</p>




